ned with one goal in mind: making auto transport as easy as possible. Leverage the latest in industry trends, data, and user-friendly features, empowering carriers, shippers, and brokers to achieve operational excellence.\n\nFrom minimizing paperwork to reducing wasted time and cutting costs, we tackle the challenges of the industry head-on, so you can focus on what you do best.\n\nWelcome to Super Dispatch, where the future of auto transport is already a reality.\n\nAbout the role\n\nSuper Dispatch is seeking a Senior Product Designer to lead design for SuperPay — the integrated payments experience that connects shippers, brokers, and carriers across the Super Dispatch ecosystem. SuperPay powers how money moves inside both Shipper and Carrier TMS, enabling fast, transparent, and secure financial transactions at scale.\n\nIn this role, you'll simplify complex payment workflows, design intuitive and trustworthy financial experiences, and create solutions that help users get paid faster while reducing operational friction.\n\nYou'll collaborate with cross-functional partners — including product, engineering, finance, and data — to define the future of how payments are managed and automated in logistics.\n\nThis is a remote-first role and an exciting opportunity to design one of the most advanced SaaS products in auto transport.\n\nSuper Dispatch is a 100% distributed team so this role can be done anywhere in the (Central Asia/Eastern Europe) .\n\nAbout You\n\nWe're looking for a customer-obsessed problem solver who thrives in complexity. You can quickly turn ambiguous problems into elegant solutions, collaborate across disciplines, and use data and AI to inform your design process. You often experiment, learn fast, and seek impact over perfection.\n\nThis is a chance to help redefine the logistics industry with design, AI, and technology.\n\nResponsibility\n\nUnderstand and map the end-to-end payment experience across Shipper and Carrier TMS platforms.\nDesign intuitive, trustworthy payment workflows — from setup and onboarding to instant transfer, arbitration, and reconciliation.\nCollaborate with PMs, engineers, and finance teams to ship high-quality designs that balance usability, security, and compliance.\nPrototype and test payment interactions using tools like Figma, Lovable, and user testing sessions with carriers and shippers.\nLeverage AI-powered design tools to explore and validate ideas quickly.\nEnsure clarity and confidence in every payment step through clear microcopy, visual feedback, and transparent status states.\nContribute to the Super Dispatch Design System, expanding it with components tailored for financial and transactional UX.\nMonitor success metrics — e.g., reduction in payment support tickets, improved payment completion time, and adoption rate of Instant Transfers.\nCollaborate cross-functionally to align payment UX with Super Dispatch's broader ecosystem (Trust, Shipper TMS, Carrier TMS).\n\nMinimum requirements\n\n5+ years of professional product design experience, ideally in a product-led environment.\nSkilled in research and discovery: customer interviews, journey mapping, usability testing, and turning insights into product opportunities.\nStrong prototyping skills, able to explore multiple solutions quickly using Figma, and AI-powered tools (e.g. Figma Make, Lovable).\nExperience working in cross-functional squads with PMs, engineers, and data teams in an agile environment.\nStrong communication skills , able to tell the story of problems and solutions clearly to stakeholders.\nFamiliarity with banking UX patterns, real-time payments, or financial data visualization.\n\nPlus points\n\nExperience with logistics, marketplace, or fintech products.\nUnderstanding of fraud prevention, verification, or trust systems.\nKnowledge of AI-assisted prototyping and how to test with synthetic users.\n\nWho you are\n\nAnalytical & systems thinker: You connect the big picture with precise execution, and design with scale in mind.\nCurious & experimental: You generate multiple approaches, test quickly (often with AI), and learn from outcomes.\nCommunicator & storyteller: You can frame customer problems and design solutions clearly for both technical and business audiences.\nCustomer-focused: You deeply empathize with shippers and brokers, and keep their needs at the center of product decisions.\nAdaptive & collaborative: You thrive in ambiguity, adjust quickly to change, and value teamwork over ego.\nOutcome-driven: You measure success by impact, not output, and push for solutions that move the business and customer forward.\n\nGrowth Plan\n\nWithin 1 month, you'll…\n\nGraduate from Super Dispatch's onboarding program and get familiar with our people, processes, and product ecosystem.\nDeeply explore how SuperPay works within Shipper and Carrier TMS, learning about automated and manual flows, arbitration windows, and instant transfers.\nReview past research, interviews, and payment support insights to understand customer pain points related to payment delays, visibility, and trust.\nDeliver your first small UX improvement (e.g., copy or UI clarity for payment status, setup experience, or digital verification).\nPresent a short “first impressions” report to the Payments Squad with early opportunities and usability observations\n\nWithin 3 months, you'll…\n\nLead your first end-to-end design project for the Payments experience\nConduct at least 3 user research sessions (interviews or usability tests) with shippers, and carriers to uncover trust and speed friction points.\nContribute to the Design System, adding or refining payment-specific components (e.g., transaction cards, trust badges, balance visuals).\nShare your first design review presentation with cross-functional stakeholders — PM, EM, and CPO — highlighting your design reasoning and impact.\n\nWithin 6 months, you'll…\n\nOwn multiple design initiatives within the Payments domain, improving clarity, transparency, and automation in how users send and receive payments.\nDeliver measurable UX impact — e.g., reducing payment-related support tickets, improving time-to-payment, or increasing adoption of Instant Transfer.\nCollaborate with the analytics team to define and monitor design KPIs (e.g., payment completion rate, NPS for financial flows).\nMentor or support a peer designer through design critiques and collaborative sessions on financial UX patterns.\nHelp establish experimentation practices in the squad — encouraging data-informed iteration and usability validation before launch.\n\nWithin 12 months, you'll…\n\nBecome the design lead for Payments, driving the product vision for how SuperPay connects Shipper and Carrier TMS.\nShape and ship at least one strategic redesign or new capability (e.g., unified payment tracking dashboard, trust & reputation signals, or guaranteed payments).\nPartner with engineering and product teams to deliver payment experiences that balance compliance, security, and usability.\nLead internal UX workshops focused on designing for trust, automation, and transparency.\nBe recognized across Super Dispatch as a go-to expert for fintech and payment UX, setting standards for future financial experience design across squads.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nGreat Culture - We strive for transparency and you'll work with like minded highly motivated people excited about solving complex problems\nRemote First Culture - We're a 100% distributed team!\nGym/Wellness Stipend - We provide a monthly stipend for gym memberships ($50/month)\nGenerous Time Off Flex PTO policy so you can take the time you need, when you need it, as well as 6–12 weeks paid paternity leave\nGreat gear – we'll set you up for success with the right tech and help you outfit your home office, if needed.\n\nLocation Requirement:\n\nWe're especially interested in candidates located in Eastern European or Central Asian regions.\n\nDoes this sound like you? We'd love to hear from you if so."}
